      <abstract id="ABS3" abstract-type="summary">
        <title>eTOC:</title>
        <p id="P5">Tripathy et al. show that mutations in <italic>MAST1</italic>, a
microtubule associated protein, cause a syndrome characterised by an enlarged
corpus callosum. They attribute this thickening to an increase in the number of
contralateral projections despite extensive cortical apoptosis.</p>
